s forewords by Anahareo’s daughters, Katherine Swartile and Anne Gaskell, an afterword by Sophie McCall, and reintroduces readers to a very important but largely forgotten text by one of Canada’s most talented Aboriginal writers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConservationistszCanadavBiography. 0aIndians of North AmericazCanadavBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Native Americans.2bisacsh1 aGaskell, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCall, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwartile, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088755455140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780887554551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780887554551/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles